## English

### About
Join innovative European technology companies from anywhere in the world. Work remotely with option to relocate to Europe when you're ready.

### 🎯 What We Offer
- **🏠 Remote-First**: Work from China (or anywhere) with European time zone flexibility
- **✈️ Optional Relocation**: Move to Europe later with full visa sponsorship & support
- **💰 Competitive Pay**: €60k-140k+ based on experience and location
- **🌍 Global Teams**: English-speaking, distributed teams across time zones
- **📈 Growth Path**: Clear career progression, conference budget, learning stipends
- **⚖️ Work-Life Balance**: European culture - 25-30 days vacation, flexible hours, no 996
- **🛠️ Modern Stack**: Latest AI/ML tools, generous compute budget, GPU clusters

### 🔍 Open Roles
- Machine Learning Engineers
- Deep Learning Research Engineers  
- LLM/NLP Engineers
- Computer Vision Engineers
- MLOps/ML Infrastructure Engineers
- AI Research Scientists

### 📋 Requirements
- Strong expertise in PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, or similar frameworks
- Experience with modern AI: LLMs, diffusion models, RL, CV, NLP
- Open source contributions or research publications (bonus)
- Good English communication (written and verbal)
- Self-motivated and experienced with remote work
- Bachelor's degree or higher in CS, AI, Math, or equivalent experience

### 🌟 Why Work Remote for European Companies?
- **No 996 culture** - Sustainable work hours, work-life balance respected
- **Async-first collaboration** - Flexible with CN timezone overlap
- **International exposure** - Work with diverse, world-class teams
- **European benefits** - Generous vacation, professional development
- **Future optionality** - Relocate to EU whenever you want with our support

### 🗺️ Relocation Options (Optional)
**Countries**: Germany • Netherlands • UK • France • Switzerland • Sweden • Portugal

**Support Provided**:
- Full visa sponsorship and immigration support
- Relocation package
- Housing assistance
- Settlement support for you and family

### 💬 Application Process
1. Submit your GitHub profile + resume/CV
2. Initial screening call (CN timezone friendly)
3. Technical assessment (take-home project or live coding)
4. Team fit conversation
5. Offer + onboarding

